  "text": "17-bp motif with seven copies in C. nudipinnis, and a 145-bp motif with three copies in P. flavilatus (Figure 3 ). The AT contents of the CRs reach up to 64.4% to 66.7%, which are higher than those of the whole mtDNA sequences. The symbolic structures of the CRs are observed as in other fishes (Figure 3) , including the extended termination associated sequence (ETAS, containing TAS-cTAS: TACAT-ATGTA), central conserved sequence blocks (CSB-F,E,D), G-BOX (GTGGGGG), pyrimidine tract (poly-T), and conserved sequence blocks (CSB 2-3) [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] ).",
